# Extremism(Homegrown, Left-Wing, etc), Lone-Wolf attacks and Cyberterrorism.
# 
# So, why is terrorism important. Terrorism has impacted our nation in various ways. Here are some examples
# of the impacts of terrorism. The safety and security of other individuals and communities were threatened. 
# political instability has happened. And, there have been severe economic consequences. So,
# Understanding terrorism helps us craft informed policies, protect citizens, and maintain social cohesion.

In [857]:
terrorismdata = pd.read_csv('plots.csv',sep=',')
terrorismdata.insert(8,'pains',0)
rowindex = 0

for row in terrorismdata.iterrows():

    if np.isnan(terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'victims_wounded']) == False or np.isnan(terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'victims_killed']) == False:

        if np.isnan(terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'victims_wounded']) == True:

            terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'victims_wounded'] = 0

        if np.isnan(terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'victims_killed']) == True:

            terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'victims_killed'] = 0

        terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'pains'] = terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'victims_wounded'] + terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'victims_killed']

    else:

        terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'pains'] = 0

        
        
    rowindex += 1

terrorismdata.insert(9,'years',0)
plots = terrorismdata['plot_name']
stringindex = 0
year = ""
rowindex = 0

for plot in plots:

    stringindex = 0
    year = ""
    
    while stringindex < 4:

        year += plot[stringindex]
        stringindex += 1

    terrorismdata.loc[rowindex,'years'] = int(year)
    rowindex += 1

years = terrorismdata['years']
pains = terrorismdata['pains']
years = np.array(years).reshape(216,1)
pains = np.array(pains).reshape(216,1)
years_b = np.c_[np.ones((216,1)),years]
theta_best = np.linalg.inv(years_b.T.dot(years_b)).dot(years_b.T).dot(pains)
pains_pred = years_b.dot(theta_best)
plt.scatter(years,pains)
plt.plot(years, pains_pred, 'r-', label='line of best fit')
plt.xlabel('time')
plt.ylabel('pains')
plt.title('pains over time')

grouped = terrorismdata.groupby("plot_ideology")
terrorismdataforthisgroup = None
pains = None
width = None
time = None
minyear = np.min(np.array(years))
maxyear = np.max(np.array(years))

for group in grouped.groups.keys():

    terrorismdataforthisgroup = terrorismdata[terrorismdata["plot_ideology"] == group]
    pains = terrorismdataforthisgroup['pains']
    time = terrorismdataforthisgroup['years']
    plt.scatter(time,pains)
    time = np.array(time).reshape(len(time),1)
    pains = np.array(pains).reshape(len(pains),1)
    time_b = np.c_[np.ones((len(time),1)),time]
    theta_best = np.linalg.inv(time_b.T.dot(time_b)).dot(time_b.T).dot(pains)
    pains_pred = time_b.dot(theta_best)
    plt.plot(time, pains_pred, 'r-', label = group)
    plt.legend(loc = 'upper left')
    

plt.xlabel('time')
plt.ylabel('pains')
plt.show()

def runML(X,Y):
    
    X = np.asarray(X).reshape(-1,1)
    Y = np.asarray(Y).reshape(-1,1)
    
    model = LinearRegression()
    
    # train the model using the training sets
    model.fit(X, Y)

    # make predictions using the testing set
    Y_pred = model.predict(X)

    print('Ordinary Least Squares (OLS)')
    print('Coefficients: ', model.coef_[0])
    print('Intercept: ', model.intercept_)
    print('Mean squared error: %.2f'
          % mean_squared_error(Y, Y_pred))
    print('Coefficient of determination: %.2f'
          % r2_score(Y, Y_pred))

    plt.scatter(X, Y,  color='black')
    plt.plot(X, Y_pred, color='blue', linewidth=3)
    
    plt.xlabel("years")
    plt.ylabel('pains')
    plt.title("pains over time")
    plt.show()
In [902]:
def runOtherML(X,Y):

    X = np.asarray(X).reshape(-1,1)
    Y = np.asarray(Y).reshape(-1,1)

    # logistic regression
    log_reg = linear_model.LogisticRegression()
    log_reg.fit(X,Y)
    lscore = log_reg.score(X, Y)
    print("Logistic Regression Accuracy: ", lscore)
    
    # SVM
    svm = SVC(gamma='auto')
    svm.fit(X, Y)
    sscore = svm.score(X, Y)
    print("SVM Accuracy: ", sscore)
    
    # KNN
    kfin = 0
    kscore = 0
    for k in range(1,21):
        knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=k)
        knn.fit(X, Y)
        score = knn.score(X, Y)
        if score > kscore:
            kfin = k
            kscore = score
        print("K Nearest Neighbors Accuracy for k = ", k, ": ", score)
        
    c1 = "red"
    c2 = "green"
    a1 = 0.55
    a2 = 1
    h = 0.5
    
    # show figures
    plt.barh(['Logistic Regression'], 1, color = c1, alpha = a1, height = h)
    plt.barh(['SVM'], 1, color = c1, alpha = a1, height = h)
    plt.barh(['KNN'], 1, color = c1, alpha = a1, height = h)

    plt.barh(['Logistic Regression'], lscore, color = c2, alpha = a2, height = h)
    plt.barh(['SVM'], sscore, color = c2, alpha = a2, height = h)
    plt.barh(['KNN'], kscore, color = c2, alpha = a2, height = h)

    plt.title("Model Accuracy")
